## ūüü° LOW Severity

### 7. Server Listens on All Interfaces

`app.listen(3000)` binds to `0.0.0.0` by default, exposing the server on all network interfaces.

**Recommendation:**
```js
const HOST = process.env.HOST || '127.0.0.1';
const PORT = process.env.PORT || 3000;
app.listen(PORT, HOST, () => {
  console.log(`Server running on ${HOST}:${PORT}`);
});
```

### 8. No Error Handling Middleware

Unhandled errors will leak stack traces to clients (**OWASP A05:2021 ‚ÄĒ Security Misconfiguration**), revealing internal paths and library versions.

**Recommendation:**
```js
// Place after all routes
app.use((err, req, res, next) => {
  console.error(err.stack); // log internally
  res.status(500).json({ error: 'Internal server error' }); // sanitized response
});

